analysis.title: Global Market Outlook
analysis.content: Neutral regime prevails amid volatility expansion. The GMS score of 52 mandates tactical equilibrium, yet the expansion of the VIX to 20.23 signals imminent regime degradation. While credit spread compression remains constructive, the flat copper-to-gold vector and decaying crypto sentiment indicate an evaporation of liquidity convexity. Market participants must navigate the fiscal-monetary nexus with vigilance as equity momentum falters, necessitating a shift toward capital preservation. [ACTION: WAIT FOR PULLBACK]
